n't a blocking issue unless I’m specifically testing logs. There's a risk in including upstream test classes if the agent requests support, so I should be cautious about that. Finally, I need to ensure I create valid JSON without any markdown.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is required before meaningful coverage is reachable. artemis-commons is a utility/common-runtime artifact with transitive compile dependencies already supplied by the artifact, and its useful APIs can be exercised with in-process unit tests.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment or system-property setup is required. If keeping Base64 coverage for 2.38.0, update tests for the current API: Base64 exposes encodeObject(Serializable), encodeBytes(byte[][, boolean]), and decode(String[, boolean]); removed members such as DONT_BREAK_LINES and decodeToObject(String) must not be used.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Upstream artemis-commons has test-scope dependencies such as artemis-unit-test-support and log4j-slf4j2-impl, but they are not needed for generated reachability tests unless copying upstream tests directly.\",\n    \"Some optional coverage areas, such as FactoryFinder, ServiceLoader-based codecs, or XML schema validation, may require test resources created under src/test/resources, but not deterministic driver setup.\",\n    \"NetworkHealthCheck can execute ping/URL checks; avoid making tests depend on external network or Docker because core commons coverage is available without it.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0a07de851fa6846b016a3f84fc2b30819482a39737dda0ee61\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5415, "output": 899, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42154, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0